Commit Message: Adding unit test directory for PyTools.
Adding TimeKeeper tests.  Modified from the PyReshaper version to account for variability in clock timing from run-to-run.
Adding Messenger unit tests.  This is a direct import from the PyReshaper repo.
Renaming to MessengerSerialTests because only the serial version of the Messenger is tested.  Need to develop a new set of tests for parallel testing.

Some refactor of the Messenger class:

Added a "split" method to the Messenger to split the MPI communicator.  

Added a "_parent" member to the Messenger to keep hold of the potentially split Messenger's parent.  

Removed the "sum" and "max" methods in favor of a "reduce" method that can apply other reduction operators in addition to "sum" and "max".  

Simplified the "print_*" methods to just one method (prinfo) with an optional parameter.  Now, there is only one print method called "prinfo", short for "print information", that takes an optional parameter "all".  If "all" is True, then it prints from all ranks.  Otherwise, if False, it only prints from the master rank.

Also, cleaned up some Messenger serial unit tests to match these changes.
Removing "serial" from test names, since all tests in this suite are serial.

Changed the "prinfo" method parameter "all" to "master" and reversed the boolean meaning.  If "master" is True, then it only prints from the master.  Otherwise, it prints from all ranks.  Also included rank number in output when printing from all ranks.

(Wanted to avoid using the "all" parameter name because it is a reserved work in Python.)
Changed the default value of the "master" parameter in the "prinfo" method.  Now defaults to "True", so that it only prints from the master.
Updated unit tests to use the new "master" parameter of the "prinfo" method.

Adding parallel unit tests for the Messenger.  To run, requires MPI and the command syntax:

mpirun -n N python messengerParallelTests.py

and the "messenger.py" module to be in the Python path.

Cleaned up the unittest output when run in parallel by capturing the output into a "string stream" (Python StringIO object) that I then message to the master rank.  I then output each
test's output in sequence with header info about to which rank the results pertain.
Updated documentation on how to run the parallel test suite.

Added test for the split mechanism.  Also, as a result of the test, I added the ability to hold on to the "color" associated with the given subcommunicator.  The color, along with the parent, should give a traceable line from subrank to parent.
Some code cleanup related to the split operation.  (Removing the 'comm' parameter from the MPIMessenger constructor.)
Added a scatter method to the messenger, with test.
Added broadcast methods to the Messenger classes.
Simple send/recv method added with tests.
Adding a 'get_color' method, just in case its useful.

Adding tests to compare output from Serial Messenger and 1-rank Parallel Messenger, to make sure the results are the same.  The point of the Messenger is to hide any need for references to MPI code, making the serial code execute with the same operations as the parallel code.

Includes a fix to the serial partition algorithm, which did not deal with sorting the data by weights since the return list in serial is the same as the list given.  However, to preserve the same order of the return list in serial and parallel, the serial code must sort the input list, too.
Renaming to make name-lengths more consistent and easier to compare names.
Do not need serial unit tests if the P1S tests (comparing 1-rank parallel results to serial results) have complete coverage of all methods.
Serial split should return a new instance of a serial Messenger, so that '_parent' and '_color' can be properly set.
No need to indicate which rank is printing test results output when running with only 1 rank.
Added a function to check if data is a Numpy NDArray.
Moving NDArray check to serial (base) class and making the method 'protected' to it is inherited.
Adding code to deal with Numpy arrays (using the mpi4py buffer send/recv calls).  All old tests continue to pass, but no new tests for new code are implemented yet.
Adding new tests of the Numpy versions.  Working on the scatter_ndarray test, which is still failing.  Need to add the bcast_ndarray and the sendrecv_ndarray tests.

Some minor cleanup in the Messenger.

Fixed tests in parallel.  Need to be VERY careful to specify the same datatype in the Numpy arrays that are being sent and recv'd.
Implemented test for sendrecv.  Fixed self-sending case and added tests.

Push/pull mechanism is now in place with tests.

I think there is a problem with this interface.  When I initially designed the interface, I assumed that gather/scatter was all that would be needed from the messenger.  With that design, the push/pull methods fit nicely into the same framework, with push/pull corresponding to gather/scatter except "vertical" in the tree of ranks.

With the addition of all of the other collective operations, just as reduce and broadcast, and the point-to-point communication method (sendrecv), this is now confusing.  I think a redesign needs to be done.

Adding a Simple Communicator class to replace the Messenger class.  It imposes a simple "master and slave" communication paradigm, such that communication is always balanced (i.e., no unbalanced sends or receives) and little more needs to be decided other than (1) whether a given rank is a master or a slave and (2) what data needs to be sent.

Also including parallel testing suite.

Adding a partitioner module to collect "partitioning functions".  These partitioning functions can be
used in send/receive calls to automatically partition data to slave ranks.

Adding defined common interface for all partitioning functions.

Adding tests for partitioning functions.
Removing old "partitioner" files and tests.  Renamed to "partfunc".

Added the ability to use a partitioning function when sending data from the master rank.  This allows for scatter-like operations, without the need to match the length of the data send to the size of the communicator.
Some minor reformating to hide some PyDev warning messages that come from Eclipse running in a serial environment and MPI4Py needing to run through mpirun for COMM_WORLD to be exposed.
Reorder some branching statements to make it more clear.  Doesn't effect code.
Consolodating some common code in the partitioning function test suite.

Changing the send/receive calls to scatter/gather calls to simplify the user interface.  Gather is simple.  Scatter has lots of options, including the use of a partitioning function and the ability to skip the 'master' rank when partitioning.

Added basic tests for this API.
Adding a check on size in the 'reduce' function.
Splitting the SimpleComm into serial and parallel version to reduce code duplication.

Added split communicator capability to the SimpleComm.  Allows the user to request a list of "sizes" for each color block.  The algorithm then computes the actual color block sizes based on the number of ranks available and the relative workload requested by the user.  The resulting split does not guarantee that the number of requested colors is preserved, nor does it guarantee that the number of ranks requested for each color block will be preserved.

Needs testing still.
Some bug fixes while adding tests of the split communicator.
Changing partitioned list scatter over split communicators test to NOT skip the intercomm scatter.  Makes more sense as a usable example.

Got some new design ideas from Ben (Jamroz) to address some corner-case issues with the old design.  Incorporating the new changes.

Needs testing.
Another redesign.  Now simplifies the communication a lot and allows communication parallel to and perpendicular to the "color dimension" and the "rank dimension" when split.

New attempt to make the partitioning functions separate classes.

Needs testing.
Finished adding the Numpy NDArray support.

Converted all of the partition functions to classes with a common base class.  Now can type-check the partition functions.  Converted the tests to this format.

Also added an equal-length partition that partitions the data into contiguous chunks.  Added test for EqualLength function.
Moved the group and color ID to the base class so that get_color and get_group can be inherited.
Removing old named partition function files.

Adding a partition function test to work with Numpy arrays.

Some partition functions create copies of the data that may not be efficient with large Numpy arrays.
Bugfix while testing the SimpleComm in parallel.  Need to copy NDArray partitions over to a new NDArray before sending via MPI, or the array is not contiguous and the process can hang.
Added sync method, which I forgot.
Added Collect tests for int, list, and arrays.

Changing the 'collect' call to return a tuple of (rank, data).  Thus, you can get the individual rank of the worker that sent the data for collection.  This can be useful for sorting or rearranging the data.  This can simply be ignored by using collect()[1] to get the data component.

Updated the tests to accound for the new return signature of the collect method.
Adding new 1-rank parallel vs serial tests.
Reformatting the docstrings to use a more readable syntax, one consistent with the Doxypypy Doxygen filter.
Added an asynchronous method to send data from the manager to the workers.  This will allow work-rationing.
Adding tests for the ration function.
Adding checks for exception errors in serial tests.
Bugfix: 'split' method of mpi4py communicator doesn't exist.  Needs to be 'Split'
Adding more setUp data so that expected values are easier to compute.
Finished tests for parallel communication with division.
Changing the name of the 'partitioning' module to 'partition'.  Just because it's shorter.

Adding a verbosity-enabled printer class.  With tests.

It is designed to work easily with the parallel SimpleComm object, as a header can be written (e.g., with rank and size info) for messages if a 'header=is_manager()' argument is passed to the print function.  The header or verbosity level can be changed easily.
Removing the old messanger from the package.  It is not needed any more.
Added a Duplicate partition function and removed the __call__ method from the base class, so it is not callable as a partition function.

Changed the default behavior of the partition method to use a one-line (no type-checking) EqualStride partition function, though this does not impose a dependency on the partition module.

Chnaged all tests to accommodate this change.

Added a constructor argument to the TimeKeeper class to allow the user to specify a different time measurement function.  By default, it is 'time.time', but it could easily be replaced with mpi4py.Wtime(), for example.
Adding a TreeGather and a TreeScatter test to the division tests.
Adding some documentation about the rationing method.
Removing the need to check the refcount of the MPI communicator, since '__del__' is only called when the object's ref count is about to go to 0 anyway.
Removing "magic numbers" from the SimpleCommMPI communication methods.
Updating partition methods to use an Abstract Base Class, so that the PartitionFunction base class can be more safely extended.
Defining a common interface to the __call__ method of the PartitionFunction.  Cannot be enforced in Python, but this makes it easier to extend.
Fixing comments for formatting by Doxypypy.
Fixing some comments per Doxypypy standards.
Renaming the get_order method to get_names, since it makes more sense.
